<paragraph blockId="33.[189,310,1479,1505]" box="[189,310,1479,1505]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1479,1505]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1479,1505]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[187,1399,1526,1732]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[189,390,1526,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bore">
<emphasis box="[189,390,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Myrmeleon bore</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be characterized by wholly dark brown vertex without yellow markings and the pronotum with lateral margins narrowly yellow on proximal half (
<bibRefCitation author="Aspock H. &amp; Aspock U. &amp; Holzel H." box="[1044,1278,1562,1588]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref15336" refString="Aspock H., Aspock U. &amp; Holzel H. 1980. Die Neuropteren Europas. Eine Zusammenfassende Darstellung der Systematik, Okologie und Chorologie der Neuropteroidea (Megaloptera, Raphidioptera, Planipennia) Europas. 2 Volumes. Goecke &amp; Evers, Krefeld, Germany." type="book" year="1980">
Aspöck 
<emphasis box="[1145,1208,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
1980
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 822; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abraham L. &amp; Papp Z." box="[189,455,1598,1627]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="137 - 139" refId="ref15167" refString="Abraham L. &amp; Papp Z. 1991. Myrmeleon bore (Tjeder, 1941) in Hungary (Planipennia, Myrmeleontidae). Neuroptera International 6: 137 - 139." type="journal article" year="1991">Ábrahám &amp; Papp 1991</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monserrat V. J. &amp; Acevedo F." box="[540,862,1598,1625]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="283 - 321" refId="ref17534" refString="Monserrat V. J. &amp; Acevedo F. 2013. Los mirmeleonidos (hormigas-leon) de la Peninsula Iberica e Islas Baleares (Insecta, Neuropterida, Neuroptera, Myrmeleontidae). Graellsia 69: 283 - 321. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / graellsia. 2013. v 69.098" type="journal article" year="2013">Monserrat &amp; Acevedo 2013</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 39; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tillier P. &amp; Giacomino M. &amp; Colombo R." box="[961,1165,1598,1624]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref19235" refString="Tillier P., Giacomino M. &amp; Colombo R. 2013. Atlas de repartition des fourmilions en France (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae). Revue de l'Association Roussillonnaise d'Entomologie 22: 1 - 51." type="journal article" year="2013">
Tillier 
<emphasis box="[1039,1097,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 13; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abraham L. &amp; Giacomino M." pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="21 - 72" refId="ref15125" refString="Abraham L. &amp; Giacomino M. 2020. A little known and synonym ant-lions 2 (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae). Natura Somogyiensis 34: 21 - 72. https: // doi. org / 10.24394 / NatSom. 2020.34.21" type="journal article" year="2020">Ábrahám &amp; Giacomino 2020</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3), while the species recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[884,983,1634,1660]" name="Pakistan" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
have yellow markings on a vertex in dorsal view and the pronotum medially brownish yellow (
<bibRefCitation author="Akhtar S. &amp; Ashfaq M. &amp; Zia A. &amp; Ali S. &amp; Ali G. M. &amp; Farhatullah &amp; Zafar Y." box="[903,1118,1670,1696]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="180 - 190" refId="ref15228" refString="Akhtar S., Ashfaq M., Zia A., Ali S., Ali G. M., Farhatullah &amp; Zafar Y. 2018. First report and redescription of five species of genus Myrmeleon (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae) from Pakistan. Journal of Biodiversity and Environmental Sciences 13: 180 - 190." type="journal article" year="2018">
Akhtar 
<emphasis box="[992,1051,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2a). This character suggests that the specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[584,683,1706,1732]" name="Pakistan" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
identified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[841,1023,1706,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmelon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bore">
<emphasis box="[841,1023,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Myrmelon bore</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belong to a different species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[189,303,1772,1798]" box="[189,303,1772,1798]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1772,1798]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1772,1798]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[188,1399,1819,2025]" lastBlockId="34.[189,1399,265,363]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[189,387,1819,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bore">
<emphasis box="[189,387,1819,1845]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Myrmeleon bore</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems widely distributed in the Palaearctic Region and was recently recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[189,292,1855,1881]" name="Pakistan" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
. Notably, 
<taxonomicName authority="Navas, 1912" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[408,711,1855,1881]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Enza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="otiosus">
<emphasis box="[408,558,1856,1881]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Enza otiosus</emphasis>
Navás, 1912
</taxonomicName>
has long been considered a secondary synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[1306,1397,1855,1881]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bore">
<emphasis box="[1306,1397,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M. bore</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stange L. A." box="[196,346,1891,1917]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 565" refId="ref19159" refString="Stange L. A. 2004. A systematic catalog, bibliography and classification of the world antlions (Insecta: Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute 74: 1 - 565." type="journal article" year="2004">Stange 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sekimoto S." box="[357,538,1891,1917]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref19027" refString="Sekimoto S. 2014. Review of Japanese Myrmeleontidae (Neuroptera). Insecta Matsumurana (N. S.) 70: 1 - 87." type="journal article" year="2014">Sekimoto 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wang X. L. &amp; Zhan Q. B. &amp; Wang A. Q." box="[549,752,1891,1917]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref19296" refString="Wang X. L., Zhan Q. B. &amp; Wang A. Q. 2018. Fauna Sinica Insecta Vol. 68 Neuroptera Myrmeleontoidea. Science Press, Beijing. [In Chinese]." type="book" year="2018">
Wang 
<emphasis box="[622,673,1891,1917]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). However, based on the priority of the nomenclature of the ICZN (International Code of Zoological Nomenclature), the validity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[1062,1178,1927,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Enza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="otiosus">
<emphasis box="[1062,1178,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">E. otiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be restored and transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[405,540,1962,1988]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[405,540,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Myrmeleon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, then 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[613,706,1962,1988]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bore">
<emphasis box="[613,706,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M. bore</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a synonym of the former. Meanwhile, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuwayama S." box="[189,411,1998,2025]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="325 - 412" refId="ref16948" refString="Kuwayama S. 1962. A revisional synopsis of the Neuroptera in Japan. Pacific Insects 4: 325 - 412." type="journal article" year="1962">Kuwayama (1962)</bibRefCitation>
did not treat 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[578,697,1999,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Enza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="otiosus">
<emphasis box="[578,697,1999,2024]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">E. otiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[927,1022,1998,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bore">
<emphasis box="[927,1022,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M. bore</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formally. Considering the type localities between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[411,529,266,291]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Enza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="otiosus">
<emphasis box="[411,529,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">E. otiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[544,649,265,291]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">holotype</typeStatus>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[688,757,265,291]" name="Japan" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Japan</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[825,919,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bore">
<emphasis box="[825,919,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. bore</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[934,1038,265,291]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">syntypes</typeStatus>
in 
